      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 58: The height-driven resize path clamps `newWidth` to `minimumWidth` but leaves `newHeight` unchanged, so small heights can produce a window that no longer matches the video aspect ratio. If preserving aspect ratio is the goal, derive the final height again when width is clamped.\n```suggestion\n            newWidth \u003d Math.round(height / videoInvAspect);\n            if (newWidth \u003c minimumWidth) {\n                newWidth \u003d minimumWidth;\n                newHeight \u003d Math.max(minimumHeight, Math.round(newWidth * videoInvAspect));\n            } else {\n                newHeight \u003d height;\n            }\n```",
